### Problem Description

Synthetic source produced via fallback mechanism is not correct when using `subobjects: false` and using object arrays.

### Steps to Reproduce

```
PUT /my_index
{
  "mappings": {
    "_source": { "mode": "synthetic" },
    "subobjects": false,
    "properties": {
      "obj": {
        "properties": {
          "k": {
              "type": "keyword",
              "doc_values": false
          }
        }
      }
    }
  }
}
```

```
PUT my_index/_doc/1
{
  "obj": [{"k": "key1"}, {"k": "key2"}]
}
```

```
GET /my_index/_doc/1

// Produces
"_source": {
    "obj.k": "key2"
}
```



### Logs (if relevant)

_No response_

```
curl -u elastic:password -H "Content-Type: application/json" "127.0.0.1:9200/test" -XPUT -d '{
  "mappings": {
        "properties": {
            "x": {
                "type": "long"
            },
            "y": {
                "type": "long"
            }
        }
  }
}'

from test, some_missing_index
```

This doesn't cause an `IndexNotFoundException` anymore, like it did in 8.15.

This is not the same as https://github.com/elastic/elasticsearch/issues/104987 because the index name does not use a wildcard, in which case it's reasonable to be more lenient.

