### Problem Description

`XContentGenerator#copyCurrentEvent` does not handle `BigInteger` and `BigDecimal` numbers. It is just not handled https://github.com/elastic/elasticsearch/blob/main/libs/x-content/src/main/java/org/elasticsearch/xcontent/XContentGenerator.java#L146. As a result `copyCurrentEvent` on documents that contain such types produces invalid documents.

### Steps to Reproduce

This is a pretty elaborate way of reproducing it but that's (more or less) how it was found.

```
PUT /my_index
{
  "mappings": {
    "_source": { "mode": "synthetic" },
    "properties": {
      "obj": {
        "store_array_source": true,
        "properties": {
          "ulong": {
           "type": "unsigned_long"
          }
        }
      }
    }
  }
}

PUT my_index/_doc/1
{
  "obj": [
    {
      "ulong":18446744073709551615
    },
    {
      "ulong":1
    }
  ]
}
```

This produces a cryptic error:
```
"statusCode": 400,
    "body": {
        "error": {
            "root_cause": [
                {
                    "type": "document_parsing_exception",
                    "reason": "[1:84] failed to parse: [1:11] Unexpected character ('}' (code 125)): was expecting a colon to separate field name and value\n at [Source: (byte[])\"[{\"ulong\"},{\"ulong\":1}]\"; line: 1, column: 11]"
                }
            ],
            "type": "document_parsing_exception",
            "reason": "[1:84] failed to parse: [1:11] Unexpected character ('}' (code 125)): was expecting a colon to separate field name and value\n at [Source: (byte[])\"[{\"ulong\"},{\"ulong\":1}]\"; line: 1, column: 11]",
            "caused_by": {
                "type": "x_content_parse_exception",
                "reason": "[1:11] Unexpected character ('}' (code 125)): was expecting a colon to separate field name and value\n at [Source: (byte[])\"[{\"ulong\"},{\"ulong\":1}]\"; line: 1, column: 11]",
                "caused_by": {
                    "type": "json_parse_exception",
                    "reason": "Unexpected character ('}' (code 125)): was expecting a colon to separate field name and value\n at [Source: (byte[])\"[{\"ulong\"},{\"ulong\":1}]\"; line: 1, column: 11]"
                }
            }
        },
        "status": 400
    },
```



### Logs (if relevant)

Stack trace points to:
```
"org.elasticsearch.xcontent.impl@8.16.0-SNAPSHOT/org.elasticsearch.xcontent.provider.json.JsonXContentParser.newXContentParseException(JsonXContentParser.java:52)"
"org.elasticsearch.xcontent.impl@8.16.0-SNAPSHOT/org.elasticsearch.xcontent.provider.json.JsonXContentParser.nextToken(JsonXContentParser.java:62)"
"org.elasticsearch.server@8.16.0-SNAPSHOT/org.elasticsearch.index.mapper.DocumentParser.parseObjectOrNested(DocumentParser.java:322)"
"org.elasticsearch.server@8.16.0-SNAPSHOT/org.elasticsearch.index.mapper.DocumentParser.parseObjectOrField(DocumentParser.java:434)"
"org.elasticsearch.server@8.16.0-SNAPSHOT/org.elasticsearch.index.mapper.DocumentParser.doParseObject(DocumentParser.java:523)"
"org.elasticsearch.server@8.16.0-SNAPSHOT/org.elasticsearch.index.mapper.DocumentParser.parseNonDynamicArray(DocumentParser.java:719)"
"org.elasticsearch.server@8.16.0-SNAPSHOT/org.elasticsearch.index.mapper.DocumentParser.parseObject(DocumentParser.java:511)"
